The WKS check is no longer recommended as part of MX processing.

The basic problem with WKS, regardless of its merits vis-a-vis other
ways of encoding the same data, is that nobody seems to be really
interested in maintaining this information.  If you look at some of the
dubious encodings in HOSTS.TXT, you will see that the DNS didn't create
the problem, though we should have been clever enough to see it coming.

paul

